        <TextBlock x:Name="Paragraph" HorizontalAlignment="Left" TextWrapping="Wrap" VerticalAlignment="Top" Margin="4,27,0,0" FontFamily="Bebas Kai" FontSize="16" Width="421"><Run Text="#include statements allows the programmer to access external or separate files called header files. The header files contains predefined   C++ routines that the programmer can use. "/><LineBreak/><Run Text="Headers file are like apps for a phone. They are an extension to the phone themselves, but are not needed to use the phone. "/><LineBreak/><Run Text="There are two forms of #include statements:"/><LineBreak/><LineBreak/><Run/></TextBlock>
